verbose_text: In AD, the cholinergic system is affected due to various processes including the following : (1) Altered NGF maturation, (2) Skewed TrkA / p75 receptor ratio, (3) Inefficient axonal transport and signaling, (4) Abeta induced modulation of NGF receptors, (5) Suboptimal ACh innervation induced inflammatory response, and (6) Abeta cytotoxicity.
